    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_003/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The candidate task card describes a software engineering / DevOps task (cross-platform deployment of a Shiny web interface), but the paper is a scientific methods paper focused on LC-MS quantification and drift correction strategies.",
        "The paper's abstract and results discuss analytical chemistry methodology (calibration, drift correction, quantification accuracy) with no mention of software architecture, user interface frameworks, or deployment infrastructure.",
        "The card appears to conflate QuantyFey (the analytical tool described in the paper) with a hypothetical software engineering project to extend its platform support. This is a fundamental scope mismatch."
